Life at F5 is never dull! For over 20 years, we have been the industry leader in application delivery; and today, we are helping our customers thrive in the new cloud future. The world\u2019s largest enterprises, service providers, financial and educational institutions, government entities, and consumer brands rely on F5 to stay ahead of security, cloud, and mobility trends.

Position Summary

Subject matter expert of Global eTime. Work and coordinate with global eTime teams and ADP to support deployments, upgrades, enhancements and to align eTime policies worldwide. Will also provide back up for monthly and semi-monthly payroll for Latin America using ADP Streamline in compliance with all applicable federal, state and local regulations. This includes but not limited to providing New Hire, Salary and Benefit changes to ADP Streamline and reviewing all changes using ADP Streamline reports. Research any payroll issues that arise in a professional and timely manner. Latin America Countries processed are Mexico, Brazil, Chile, Colombia and Argentina.

Primary Responsibilities
  • Worldwide eTime SME
  • Work and coordinate with global eTime teams and ADP to support deployments, upgrades, enhancements and align eTime policies worldwide.
  • Process payments, adjustments, special pay, and vacation pay
  • Process Sodexo file where applicable
  • Process Savings fund where applicable
  • Provide New Hire, Salary changes, Benefit changes and Terminations directly to vendor
  • Review post processing reports to validate payroll for accuracy and completeness
  • Provide reporting to Accounting Vendor for Journal entries
  • Available to answer and research complex payroll related issues with employees, human resources, accounting and legal
  • Responsible for upholding F5\u2019s Business Code of Ethics and for promptly reporting violations of the Code or other company policies.
  • Process and calculate pay upon termination with vendor assistance
  • Generate reports from HR system (Workday) to validate Salary, Allowance, Manager, Job changes in addition to New Hires and Terminations.
  • Performs other related duties as assigned.
The Job Description is intended to be a general representation of the responsibilities and requirements of the job. However, the description may not be all-inclusive, and responsibilities and requirements are subject to change.

Knowledge, Skills And Abilities
  • Proficient in Microsoft Office, especially excel
  • Proven ability to work in a fast paced environment
  • Ability to meet or exceed deadlines
  • Experience with ADP Streamline preferred
  • Experience with Workday preferred
  • Experience with ADP Etime preferred
  • High level of confidentiality is required
  • Strong written and verbal communication skills
  • Excellent at problem solving
Qualifications
  • 5+ years\u2019 experience in payroll processing preferred
Physical Demands and Work Environment
  • Duties are performed in a normal office environment while sitting at a desk or computer table.
  • Duties require the ability to utilize a computer, communicate over the telephone, and read printed material.
  • Duties may require being on call periodically or working outside normal working hours (evenings and weekends).
  • This position will be part of the Payroll team that is located in Seattle. F5 Networks, Inc. is an equal opportunity employer and strongly supports diversity in the workplace.
